snippet.title: Fujifilm Instax Share SP-1
snippet.description: The company extends its analog Instax line into digital with a new portable Wi-Fi printer.

snippet.title: Olloclip 4-in-1 Photo Lens for iPad
snippet.description: The clip-on photo lens maker for iPhone and iPod touch will have a new one just for the iPad.

snippet.title: Olloclip Macro 3-in1 Photo Lens for iPhone
snippet.description: For iPhone photographers who want to get closer to the world around you, this is the lens to do it with.

snippet.title: Twitter for iOS
snippet.description: The official Twitter apps for iOS offer reliable performance and slick design, but power users may find themselves wanting more.

snippet.title: Carousel (iOS)
snippet.description: If you don't mind the 5GB storage limit, Carousel is an excellent way to share photos and videos.

snippet.title: KitCamera for iOS
snippet.description: KitCamera is a must-have for mobile photographers with tons of tools and effects, along with fine-tuning controls to help you get the perfect shot.

snippet.title: FX Photo Studio (iOS)
snippet.description: FX Photo Studio stands out for the sheer number of effects that are available, but it can be a struggle to get the app to do what you want.

snippet.title: Groopic for iOS
snippet.description: Groopic is a must-have for getting the photographer into a group shot, with an easy-to-understand process, filters to spice up your picture, and mostly flawless results.

snippet.title: PhotoMotion
snippet.description: If you just want an easy way to create a slideshow with neat zooming effects, PhotoMotion is a great choice, but music limitations and a lack of extras leave you wanting more.
